                prodLink: 'The 5-step loop (zero_grad → forward → loss → backward → step) is inviolable. Production additions: clip_grad_norm_ between backward and step; log total gradient norm to WandB every N steps — a sudden 10× spike means exploding gradients. Use torch.autograd.detect_anomaly() during debug sessions to find the exact operation producing NaN. Never inline multiple backward calls into a complex expression — debug by isolating each gradient computation.',
