For L layers: ∂L/∂W₁ ≈ ∂L/∂aₗ · ∏ᵢ (Wᵢ · σ'(zᵢ))

Vanishing gradients — product < 1:
  Sigmoid max gradient = 0.25; for 10 layers: 0.25^10 ≈ 10^{-6}
  Early layers receive near-zero gradient → stop learning
  Symptom: loss decreases slowly; early-layer weights barely change; grad norms → 0

Exploding gradients — product > 1:
  Product grows exponentially → gradient norms spike to Inf or NaN
  Symptom: loss goes to NaN; weight norms diverge; training stops after a few steps

Three structural fixes:

1. Better activations:
   ReLU gradient = 1 for x > 0 (no compression in positive region)
   ResNet skip: ∂(F(x)+x)/∂x = ∂F(x)/∂x + 1 ≥ 1 (identity gradient path)

