  m_t = β₁·m_{t-1} + (1-β₁)·g_t       (1st moment: mean of gradient)
  v_t = β₂·v_{t-1} + (1-β₂)·g_t²      (2nd moment: uncentred variance)
  m̂_t = m_t / (1-β₁ᵗ)                 (bias correction — critical early in training)
  v̂_t = v_t / (1-β₂ᵗ)
  w_t = w_{t-1} - η · m̂_t / (√v̂_t + ε)
  Defaults: β₁=0.9, β₂=0.999, ε=1e-8, η=1e-3

